answer_found_by_llm: The suspicious process  "oneetx.exe" (PID 5896), spawned a child process "rundll32.exe" (PID 7732).

No explicit memory protection settings could be retrieved for the suspicious process (PID 4628) using Volatility's vadinfo and malfind plugins. The analysis tools returned no data for this process, suggesting it may have exited prior to the memory dump or had non-suspicious memory protections.

The process responsible for establishing the VPN connection is "Outline.exe", as it is the parent of "tun2socks.exe" (PID 4224) and part of a known VPN client framework. The network tunneling activity observed via "tun2socks.exe" supports this conclusion.
The attacker's IP address identified from network connections is **38.121.43.65**, observed in TCP connections to port 443 (HTTPS) initiated by the tunneling process "tun2socks.exe".
The full URL of the PHP file visited by the attacker is **http://dongtaiwang.com/loc/phome.php?v=**, observed multiple times in the memory dump's HTTP-related strings.
The full path of the malicious executable is **\Users\Tammam\AppData\Local\Temp\c3912af058\oneetx.exe**.
